"within a 2-𝜎 confidence level. By contrast, maximum masses with 𝑀TOV & 2.5 𝑀�, not only require efficiencies
in the gravitational-wave emission that are well above the numerical-relativity estimates, but they also lead to
a significant under-production of the ejected mass. Hence, the tension can be released by assuming that the
secondary in GW190814 was a black hole at merger, although it could have been a rotating neutron star before."
